Statusline "task:" row — auto-generated ≤5-word session description.

Install:
  1. Copy scripts/statusline-command.sh and scripts/statusline-task-summary.sh
     to ~/.claude/ and chmod +x them. statusline-task-summary.sh has the
     claude binary path hardcoded (CLAUDE_BIN) — adjust per machine.
  2. Wire up ~/.claude/settings.json as below.

How it works: the UserPromptSubmit hook detaches a background
`claude -p --model haiku` call per prompt and writes a short summary to
/tmp/claude-statusline-task-<session_id>; the statusline script renders it
as a second row ("task: Reviewing PR 82"), falling back to session_name.
CC_TASKLINE=1 is the guard env var: it stops the hook from re-triggering
itself inside the nested claude call and silences the chime hooks there
(see Hooks/done_sound for the guarded chime commands).

settings.json wiring:

"statusLine": {
  "type": "command",
  "command": "bash /home/linco/.claude/statusline-command.sh"
},
"hooks": {
  "UserPromptSubmit": [
    {
      "hooks": [
        {
          "type": "command",
          "command": "bash /home/linco/.claude/statusline-task-summary.sh"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
